claim.claim-text:
An apparatus (500) comprising:
a base frame having a turntable (530);
a vertical section (550) configured to be mounted on the turntable (530) via a slidable mounting platform (552), the vertical section (550) having a tapered wedge (600) configured to move up and down the vertical section (550);
wherein the turntable (530) is configured to rotate at least 360 degrees, and the vertical section (550) is configured to move in a radial direction with respect to a center of rotation of the turntable (530).

A method for removing a stator coil in a stator core (50) of a dynamoelectric machine (10), the method comprising the steps of:
providing an apparatus (500) having a base section and a vertical section (550), the base section configured for supporting the stator core;
placing the stator core on the base section so that at least a portion of the vertical section (550) is inside the stator core;
aligning a wedge (600) connected to the vertical section with a stator slot (52);
driving the wedge along the stator slot to remove the stator coil.
